The paper deals with algorithms for finding optimal search trees, which is a classic problem in data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves analyzing the time complexity of the algorithms, which falls under the category of algorithms (cs.AL). The use of approximation algorithms to solve the problem suggests that it may also belong to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing and proving previous work incorrect, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the use of logarithmic time complexity suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of information theory (cs.IT).
